+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EVagKgqVFUrCNcqRQH43vk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Plugin Marketplace System\n\n### Modules\n\n1. **Plugin Registry** (`src/registry/index.ts`) - In-memory catalog storing plugin manifests keyed by name and version. Supports register, get, getVersion, list, search (by name/description/author), remove, listVersions, and update operations.\n\n2. **Version Resolver** (`src/resolver/index.ts`) - Wraps the `semver` package to resolve version constraints against available versions, check satisfaction, find max satisfying versions, and validate ranges.\n\n3. **Sandboxed Runner** (`src/runner/index.ts`) - Executes arbitrary code strings in Node.js `vm` contexts with configurable timeouts. Returns structured results with success/failure, output, timing, and memory usage. Handles cross-context Error extraction.\n\n4. **Review System** (`src/reviews/index.ts`) - Uses `better-sqlite3` with an in-memory database for persistence. Supports adding reviews, computing average ratings (excluding flagged reviews), flagging, querying by plugin/user, and counting.\n\n5. **Dependency Graph** (`src/deps/index.ts`) - Builds dependency trees, detects circular dependencies, produces topological orderings, and flattens transitive dependency lists.\n\n### Integration Layer (`src/index.ts`)\n\nExports `createMarketplace()` which composes all five services and provides `installPlugin()` that:\n- Validates required fields (name, version, entryPoint)\n- Registers the plugin in the catalog\n- Resolves dependency versions against the registry\n- Checks for circular dependencies (rejects if found)\n- Executes the entry point in the sandbox\n- Returns resolved dependencies and execution result\n\n### Test Coverage\n\n53 tests across 6 test files covering all modules and the integration layer."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{